# Architecture Rules

## Layering

- Use layered architecture: controller -> service -> dao
- Controllers coordinate requests and responses only
- Services contain business logic and orchestration
- DAOs handle persistence and data access only

## Boundaries

- Do not put business logic in controllers
- Do not access the database directly from controllers
- Keep validation and transport concerns separate from business logic
- Prefer dependency flow from controller -> service -> dao, not the reverse

## DTOs

- Use DTOs for input validation and data transfer between layers
- Validate incoming request data before it reaches business logic
- Keep DTOs focused on shape and validation, not behavior

## Example

```ts
// Avoid
async function createUserController(req, res) {
  const user = await db.users.insert({
    email: req.body.email,
    plan: applyPricingRules(req.body.plan),
  });

  res.json(user);
}
```

```ts
// Prefer
async function createUserController(req, res) {
  const input = CreateUserDto.parse(req.body);
  const user = await userService.createUser(input);
  res.json(user);
}
```

- `createUserController()` handles request and response
- `userService.createUser()` contains business rules
- `userDao` performs database operations
